ch. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Pierre Ier D'OLHAIN was born in 1188, in Fresnicourt-le-Dolmen, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France, his father, Simon d'OLHAIN, was 40 and his mother, Gisèle de RANCHICOURT, was 22. He married Giselberthe DE NÉDON about 1215. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died about 1240, at the age of 53."},"et":{"1188–environ 1240":"1188–umbes 1240","1188–1240":"1188–1240","1198–1253":"1198–1253","1219–1269":"1219–1269","1148–1195":"1148–1195","1166–1220":"1166–1220","environ 1240":"umbes 1240","1220":"1220","1253":"1253","1198":"1198","ABT 1215":"umbes 1215","1240":"1240","1195":"1195","ABT 1219":"umbes 1219","1148":"1148","1269":"1269","1188":"1188","1166":"1166","1219":"1219","Fresnicourt-le-Dolmen, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Fresnicourt-le-Dolmen, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1188–environ 1240":"1188–noin 1240","1188–1240":"1188–1240","1198–1253":"1198–1253","1219–1269":"1219–1269","1148–1195":"1148–1195","1166–1220":"1166–1220","environ 1240":"noin 1240","1220":"1220","1253":"1253","1198":"1198","ABT 1215":"noin 1215","1240":"1240","1195":"1195","ABT 1219":"noin 1219","1148":"1148","1269":"1269","1188":"1188","1166":"1166","1219":"1219","Fresnicourt-le-Dolmen, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Fresnicourt-le-Dolmen, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Ranska"},"fr":{"1188–en